      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2015-12-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2016-02-17T21:28:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Charitable Giving Privacy Protection Act </strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to prohibit the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) from requiring or accepting the Social Security account numbers of donors of charitable donations from donee organizations when such organizations are providing substantiation of such donations. The IRS may require the use of an identifier other than a Social Security account number. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
